El día de mañana llega para todas las plataformas de manera gratuito el juego completo de Destiny 2, llamado Destiny 2 New Light, en donde todos los jugadores que aún no posean el juego podrán acceder a todo el contenido del mismo así como a la primera y a la segunda expansión.

A su vez, también estará disponible la nueva expansión llamada Shadowkeep, que podrá ser adquirida por un precio de 40 USD$, en donde los jugadores podrán visitar la luna y enfrentarse a la oscuridad que allí habita.

Just completed “Among the Sleep” along with all of its trophies. It took around 4 hours to complete. ——
The game falls under the horror genre. It places you in the perspective of a baby (1st person) which works really well with the game’s aesthetic and does a good job of unnerving the player. The game overall has many beautiful level designs and the shift from being comfortable to scared through slight adjustments to the level are quite effective. The storytelling aspect of the game could’ve been more cohesive as some of the “memories” in the game can be interpreted to mean different things (similar conclusions but different connotations), this does take away slightly from the impact of the game because of the possibility of confusion but overall the game was well paced and the twist at the end was really well done. The game does tackle some heavy themes but it handles them well but (SPOILER WARNING) the reveal that the father could be abusive makes the game’s ending seem darker than it actually was before playing the prologue. Basically the baby leaves an alcoholic mother to live with a possibly abusive father (Or that’s what I understood after completing the Prologue). The controls are also a bit unusual, especially the interact button being R1 and then moving the objects you’re interacting with by using the Right analog stick, the addition of a peeking around corners mechanic makes sense for the game but honestly wasn’t necessary in the gameplay. I was they did utilize that mechanic better because it would’ve made the gameplay more fun or different. The game does have some bugs such as getting stuck between a chair and a table in multiple sections that you’ll have to wiggle your way out of and the other bug I came across had to do with attempting to go back to the main menu through the pause menu. Attempting to do so results in the game freezing so I was forced to close the game and then reopen it to continue. Overall I’d give this game a 6/10 just because I feel like if a few tweaks and revision of the game could’ve made the game far better than it was but I still think that if you’re interested you should definitely try it out.

preview_comments.text:
Just to be safe, though; the male pulled his red bandana over his face, simply waiting like a predator awaiting his prey— and eventually, the train began whizzing by. 
Instead of jumping onboard immediately, Lucifer simply listened to the clicking and clicking of the locomotive, only deciding to make his leap of faith when the last car approached. Unfortunately, though; there seemed to be a few guards onboard, and one seemed to have caught him. 
But, instead of firing shots— Lucifer quickly lunged towards the man, both of their hats falling onto the floor as Lucifer began throwing and taking punches, eventually being able to knock the man out with the butt of his own revolver. Luckily, nobody seemed to notice the sounds of violence, so Lucifer simply tossed the unconscious man off of the train, though it was still fairly close to the town. 
But, to prevent further fights, Lucifer simply placed his hat back onto his head and went as far back on the train as he could, simply hiding himself inside of a crate that was luckily empty. But now— he had to endure the trip until he reached close to his camp, where Red would be waiting. But, before he closed his eyes to attempt to rest throughout the ride, he muttered a simple sentence. “Why the hell did I leave the horses with Red?”

caption.text:
On the outskirts of the town of Rhodes, a man named Lucifer sat atop the supports for a short bridge belonging to a railway. As he often did, the male pulled a black journal from his satchel and began to write, his legs dangling casually. .
As ink began being sprawled over the paper, a cigarette met Lucifer’s lips, the faint smoke and strong smell filling the air around him. But, the man didn’t seem bothered by any of this, but this was because he was used to it all, and was of course more focused on his writing. .
“So, I finally managed to figure out the year, and even the date. Apparently it’s May the fifteenth, eighteen ninety eight. But— regardless of the damned date, a few things have happened since my last entry a few weeks ago. .
First, Red and I made another sell, though this one didn’t go so hot. Of course, we still got our money— but it was from multiple corpses. Apparently that happens quite often, but I suppose I’ve now taken the lives of... ten men? The oddest part is, I don’t even feel much remorse anymore. Ma always taught me to never kill a man unless he needs killin’— but pa viewed things... well, differently to say the least. He didn’t care if anyone died, hell— if someone looked at me wrong, that’s reason enough for me to murder in his eyes. Hell, maybe his words had merit to them— who knows?
.
Next, though; we ended up coming to the little town of Rhodes— seems like the town is in some sort of feud? The two sides are two insanely wealthy families— the inbreeding kind it seems. Seems at least one of them owns a plantation, though I’m personally going to stay well away from that shit. .
But, lastly— Red and I got completely drunk in the bar, there’s not much reason for me writing this, except for the fact that this entry seems rather sad in a way; filled with murder and undoubtedly racist rich folk. Oh well, I suppose that’ll be all— I have a train to catch.
.
-Lucifer”
.
As Lucifer placed his journal back into his satchel, he felt the ground begin to shake— showing that a train was coming down the line. Of course, the male started to climb down from the railing, doing his best to hide behind the pillar type beams
.

Ner'zhul is originally the supreme shaman of the orcs of Draenor.  Once upon a time, when the orcs had never heard of the world of humans, the commander of the Burning Legion, Kil'jaeden, appeared to Ner'zhul.  The demon saw that the shaman was very capable of magic and endowed Ner'zhul with the power to command streams of magical energy, in return for devotion to the Legion.  Ner'zhul aided the demons in the fight against the draenei living in Draenor, but soon the shaman began to realize that the orcs were only pawns in the great game of the demons of the Legion.  Kil'jaeden, realizing that Ner'zhul no longer wants to help the Legion, but has his own plans, chose a new representative of the orc race - a student of Ner'zhul, Gul'dan.  Gul'dan received even greater demonic power and authority.  Fearing for his life, Ner'zhul went into the shadows and his name was no longer mentioned in the First or Second Wars with the Alliance.

3. Silent Hill 4 (OST) by #akirayamaoka . The only composer/artist on my list. There is no other guy in the world that can make even nearly as good ambient music than this one. There is not a single week that goes by without his music. Whether it's at work, while driving my car or at home, there's always some Yamaoka involved. Hell, even my ringtone has been Wounded Warsong from this album like 7 years or so. I'm more impressed that I've been able to get some of my musician friends to listen his work actively. He can make all of his instruments and computer created sounds sound perfect. The songs that have a singer has had the artists perfectly picked. I chose this album from all the possibilities because it has imo the widest range of Yamaokas musical talent and lot's of my favorites in it. Also, It's the only album I own from him since they're nearly impossible to find these days at a reasonable price not to say even from my country. #music  #ambient #videogames #instruments #top10 #mytop10 #myplaylist

Delicious Pozole <3!!! But What is a pozole? 
The pozole is a dish that consists of a kind of broth made from corn grains of a type known as cacahuazintle, to which, depending on the region, chicken or pork meat is added as a secondary ingredient. Of this basic preparation there are variations throughout the Mexican territory. But the pozole cannot go alone, it needs classic companions such as onion, radishes and lettuce finely processed. Oregano and ground chili to sprinkle at will; in addition to the lemon and toast to accompany. Now in our time, the pozole is a dish spread throughout most of the country, the most famous are those of Jalisco, Michoacán, Tepic, Colima, Guanajuato and Guerrero. Among those who remain, of course, the white pozole that is the basic one, from which others derive. History The Pozole that in the Nahuatl language is "pozolli", means foam and is called like this because the large and white corn kernels when boiled open like flower and form foam. In a story by Fray Bernardino de Sahagún, in his general history of the things of New Spain, during the celebrations of honor of God Xipe Moctezuma was sent a well with the thigh of a prisoner and sacrificed boy. Variants Among its very diverse types are beef, chicken, vegetarian with pumpkin, zucchini and other vegetables. of seafood and even wheat. There is no doubt that the pozole is completely Mexican: the perfect hybrid of Spanish and indigenous seasonings, for its good dose of corn and pork. Incredibly, the well is one of the most representative foods of Mexican cuisine. In addition, this dish, contrary to what it might seem, is extremely nutritious and balanced.

Hello new books, goodbye TBR
.
Brace yourself, I'm gonna be posting more content this week than I probably ever will in the future. This is part of a project I did with @Bookphantom21 where we recreated some of the bookworm problems from the bookmark series by @CreativeChaotics
There were five bookmarks that we recreated, and this is the first! This was a spur of the moment decision to create these, but it was a lot of fun and I definitely want to do more Cosplay film stuff in the future. Of course when you're talking about bookworms, there was no better character in my cosplay closet than Sorey, that absolutely precious, book loving, history nerd.
I will be posting one each day this week. Joanna will be posting them as well, along with a still photo version, so go check those out as well!
.
Bookmark by @CreativeChaotics
Directed by @Bookphantom21
Camera work: @niteclover
Cosplay: Me
.

My version of mr. Dream #punchout #nintendo #videogames #artlovers #80s #cartoons #digitalpainting #digitdrawing

"VERILY!" Man, oldschool Thor sounded so cool back in the comics, spouting old English, while fighting villains! 
So, just a few thoughts i wanted to share inspired by this piece, since I kinda saw something in it. Everyone, at one point, has been down certain roads where a sense of doubt can invade your mind and really just hold you captive from achieving something for yourself because for fear of the unknown, or fear of failure. It's a rough feeling to shake off, because you cant make a move without obsessing over it, and more often than not you can find yourself in a standstill just because of it, and there's no end result, other than staying where you started. Admittedly, I saw myself tripping into this area too many times to count, but I learned that the easiest way to remedy it, was to be defiant over it. Forget the fear, forget the doubt, and instead focus on what you can achieve by taking that one step. I know it's easier said than done, but when you weigh the good over the bad, it helps reinforce your goals, really. And if you fall short, it's never game over, just another shot to take to adapt and get better. Hold strong to the things that matter, and whenever you find self-doubt and fear creeping in, say loud and proud "I SAY THEE NAY!!" And smash that fear with a metaphorical Mjolnir, but really, say it aloud, it's the coolest!

caption.text: What a GREAT new album/listen...Can’t wait to see these guys this Wednesday...Been wanting to see em since I played “Through The Fire and The Flames” when I was little on Guitar Hero🔥🎸 #DragonForce #Strangers #ExtremePowerMetal #2019 #PowerMetal #VideoGames #HeavyMetal #Shred

#FIFA20 Review ⚽️🎮
Il nuovo capitolo calcistico targato @easportsfifa.it è finalmente disponibile! Sarà riuscito a confermarsi anche quest’anno come titolo di punta del calcio visto la sempre più agguerrita concorrenza?
Ecco cosa ne pensiamo nella nostra #recensione:
Ci piace 👍🏼
- La nuova modalità Volta sostituisce la campagna Il Viaggio vista nelle passate edizioni, con una nuova storia che vi vedrà partire proprio dai campetti di strada.
- Volta rappresenta il fulcro del nuovo Fifa e la modalità più divertente del gioco, andando a richiamare l’indimenticabile Fifa Street. Potrete formare la vostra squadra e intraprendere il Tour mondiale contro le altre formazioni sia offline che online.
- La modalità carriera ora offre la possibilità delle conferenze stampa pre e post partita che possono influenzare l’umore della squadra. 
Non ci piace 👎🏼
- Qualche bug di troppo nella modalità carriera ereditato dal capitolo precedente.
- L’intelligenza artificiale presenta ancora diverse problematiche soprattutto nel gestire la fase difensiva.
- Graficamente e nella gran parte del gameplay il gioco è quello dello scorso anno, con pochi miglioramenti. Ad eccezione della modalità Volta.
Voto: 8,5

caption.text:
Hello!! Here are my first water elevators! Water elevators using bubble columns are super useful with getting around! I use it for everything - in my builds, to get to my strip mines, to get to mob farms, and soon if needed, item elevators! It’s easy to make and very efficient. Make sure you have plenty of kelp so you can make the water in the elevators into water sources a lot faster! While redstone elevators are really cool, I’d still prefer something simple, so if I could use bubble columns and have space for two - one to go up and one to go down, I’d rather do that! Also, a peek at my strip mines! I’ll share the system I use soon!

caption.text:
Soooo, Leutis! Wie immer folgt hier ein kleiner Sammelpost zur letzten Con - in dem Fall die @germancomiccon Berlin X//3 .
Die An- und Abreise verliefen dieses Mal deutlich besser als in Magdeburg - und das, obwohl wir orientierungslose Idioten sind xD Aber die Berliner haben uns ganz toll geholfen und uns super nett den Weg gewiesen Q///Q Egal, ob in der Stadt, oder auf der Con - danke für eure Hilfsbereitschaft und Freundlichkeit! 💛💙
Die GCC war jetzt die erste, etwas größere Con für uns - und wir waren ganz schön geflasht von den Hallen! 😱 Völlige Überforderung und man wusste gar nicht, wo man zuerst gucken soll x//D Außerdem war unser geliebter Kaffeewagen (@coffeebike_official) da und hat uns bei kleinen Downs immer wieder den nötigen Energieschub geliefert x//D Generell war das ganze Essen in Berlin Hammer und wir werden es vermissen QwQ Nutzt unbedingt die Lieferservices dort aus! 🍔🍱
.
Ein großes Dankeschön geht mal wieder an unseren besten Manager und Standschreier @kenjiroccosplay x//D 💛✨ Die liebe Maus ist echt die fürsorglichste und aufmerksamste Person, bedient uns gerne von vorne bis hinten (selbst, wenn wir schon schimpfen! XD) und achtet auf unser Wohl Q///Q 💙💛 Danke für alles! Wir werden dich auf der Mex nächsten Monat sehr vermissen T///T fühl dich geknuddelt bis zum Umfallen! 💙💛💙💛✨
.
Dann hatten wir zudem eine sehr liebe Standnachbarin - da haben wir echt immer wieder großes Glück x//D Es ist so schön, sich austauschen zu können Q///Q Vielen Dank für deine Tipps und dass wir uns in den Pausen so gut unterhalten haben, @tsuyonpu ✨💙💛 Wir Deppen haben eben erst gemerkt, dass wir echt die ganze Zeit miteinander zu tun und... nicht ein Selfie gemacht haben xD 🤦🏻‍♀️ Das wird nächsten Monat dann bitte nachgeholt! eve .
Und generell noch ein Dankeschön an alle süßen, lieben Leutis, für eure Unterstützung und lieben Worte! 💛💙✨Wir sehen uns auf der Mex! ✨
.

"In vain glory they arose, shouting challenges at the gods. But prevail they did not, their doom it was to walk the mist until time's end." - Fran

How about another shot of Fran?

You can get a closer view of the detailing in this one, like the twisty helm and real chain mail attached to the corset.

Her armour is actually very fragile and lightweight. It’s all made from 2mm black craft foam; one layer for the base and another for the detail strips. Sealed with some PVA glue and spray painted a matt black.

But to get that leather look, I covered the whole lot in ebony Rub ‘n’ Buff and gently polished with a soft cloth.

Photo 📷 by @si_j_spencer.

Fel (English Fel) - the extreme step of secret magic in Azeroth, demonic magic.  This energy is secret magic in its most pernicious form, because it uses the blood of demons and soul stones of other creatures.  Demonic spells are very difficult to resist.  Warlocks using demonic energy run the risk of falling into the power of the forces to which they call.  Mages who have resorted to resort to fel magic associate its use with euphoria.  If secret magic is addiction, then fel magic is a drug in its purest form, and much more dangerous: it is quickly addictive.  More often than not, a single time is enough to form a strong dependence, as was the case with the orcs.  Corruption of the personality of a sorcerer resorting to demonic magic occurs extremely quickly;  even if he does not become a slave to demons, his character often turns to evil and chaos.  The disgusting yellow-green flame is an external manifestation of fel magic, energy that has become material.  This flame is called entropic fire, it contains infernals, it consists of the "mane" of Mannoroth the Destroyer and some other lords of the underworld.  Entropic fire looks like an ordinary fire, but in fact it is much worse: it feeds on the energy of life, including the energy of life of its carrier

BATMAN EASTER EGG THAT TOOK 3 YEARS TO DISCOVER ≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈↓↓↓↓≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈
-
Rocksteady’s first Batman game, Arkham Asylum, was notable for the presence of a hidden room that took nearly a year to be discovered. This room had a map that turned out to give clues to the next game, so it’s not surprising that when the sequel came out players were desperately hunting for similar secrets.

Arkham City managed to withhold its biggest secret for three solid years, which is a miracle in the modern gaming world. If you set the date on your console to the day that Rocksteady was formed, you’ll get a message from Calendar Man that dropped some hints for the next game in the series, Arkham Knight.
